{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17605971","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17605971"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T13:07:15+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T13:07:15+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15888"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15888","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15888"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8579"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72052"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8579","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8579"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15888"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57522"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4935"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"8595"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20566"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20568"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72052","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/72052"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe placenta develops specialised cell layers during early pregnancy that are crucial for maintaining pregnancy and supporting foetal development.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the syncytiotrophoblast?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["A temporary structure present only during implantation","A layer of distinct mononuclear cells","A collection of stem cells that form the placenta","An inner cellular layer beneath the cytotrophoblast","A multinucleated layer without cell boundaries"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Emultinucleated layer without cell boundaries\u003C/strong\u003E correctly describes the syncytiotrophoblast, which forms the outer surface of placental villi. This layer develops through fusion of underlying cytotrophoblast cells and is essential for hormone production and maternal-foetal exchange.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA temporary structure present only during implantation\u003C/strong\u003E - The syncytiotrophoblast persists throughout pregnancy\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA layer of distinct mononuclear cells\u003C/strong\u003E - This describes the cytotrophoblast, not the syncytiotrophoblast\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EA collection of stem cells that form the placenta\u003C/strong\u003E - The syncytiotrophoblast is a differentiated layer, not a stem cell population\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAn inner cellular layer beneath the cytotrophoblast\u003C/strong\u003E - The syncytiotrophoblast forms the outer, not inner, layer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe syncytiotrophoblast is crucial for pregnancy maintenance through its roles in hormone production (especially human chorionic gonadotropin) and facilitating exchange between maternal and foetal circulation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["The syncytiotrophoblast is a multinucleated layer that forms the outer surface of placental villi and produces human chorionic gonadotropin.","The syncytiotrophoblast forms by fusion of underlying cytotrophoblast cells and lacks distinct cell boundaries.","The syncytiotrophoblast persists throughout pregnancy and is essential for maternal-fetal exchange."],"references":["Kojima J, Ono M, Kuji N, Nishi H. Human Chorionic Villous Differentiation and Placental Development. Int J Mol Sci. 2022 Jul 20;23(14):8003. doi: 10.3390/ijms23148003. PMID: 35887349; PMCID: PMC9325306","Jones TM, Montero FJ. Chorionic Villus Sampling. [Updated 2022 Dec 11]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK563301/","Padubidri, V. G., \u0026 Daftary, S. N. (Eds.). (2014). Shaw\u0027s Textbook of Gynecology E-book. Elsevier health sciences","Singh, V. (2022). Textbook of clinical embryology, -E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57522"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15888"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"57522","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/57522"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-20T22:05:30+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-20T22:06:25+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8579"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"72052"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":